commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, CommandResult is getting too cluttered as more functionality is being added. For instance, with the addition of the Download command, there would be 3 different constructors and an excessive number of attributes for the CommandResult class.

Hence, different classes were created for each CommandResult type, to better encapsulate the different cases where we need to change the UI on some command provided by the user. Overall, this should make the code less verbose and easier to understand and maintain.

- Cleaner if statements
- Return from handleDownload early if conditions met
- Add try-catch for JSON-related methods
- Add assertions to make code more robust
Factor out logic for trimming predicate arguments and for querying the student descriptor into separate functions, in an attemp to maintain SLAP.

commitResults.messageTitle: Set temporary regex expressions for student ID, Class ID and Grade: - Student ID: [A-Z][0-9]{7}[A-Z] (1 letter followed by 7 numbers followed by 1 letter) - Class ID: [A-Z][0-9]{2} (1 letter followed by 2 numbers) - Grade: ([AB]((\+)|-)*)|([CD](\+)*)|(F) (Letter with a sign when appropriate)
